<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-25T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-25T18:00:00-05:00" n="653" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d653">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 654.119/189</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-25T19:00:00-04:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 25, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3710. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1">McFadden</persName> [from War Trade Board]:</p>
                            <p>No. 49. Embassy’s 3660, April 19, noon. Your 41. We will act in
                                concert with other Governments represented on Contingent Commission
                                and will adopt the plan suggested in your cable by virtue of which
                                we will hereafter, in all cases where it appears that unauthorized
                                exports from Switzerland to Central Powers have taken place,
                                withhold exports of corresponding raw materials to Switzerland until
                                receipt from Swiss Government of satisfactory explanation and of an
                                assurance for the future.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>